  "text": "Propionate enters systemic circulation through the portal vein, where it is metabolised primarily in the liver while acetate is more broadly circulated, for example, crossing the blood-brain barrier, where it may influence satiety through action on the hypothalamus 190 . On the basis of murine studies, gut-derived acetate and propionate have separately been suggested to influence asthma [CITATION_1] 198, 199 . While regulatory T-cell activity is enhanced by acetate-mediated inhibition of histone deacetylase 9 (HDAC9), resulting in suppression of environmental allergen hypersensitivity, propionate affects lung dendritic cells, dampening promotion of T helper type 2 cell-driven inflammation while leaving the cells' phagocytic ability intact 81, [CITATION_2] [198] [199] [200] .",
