      "span_text": "While regulatory T-cell activity is enhanced by acetate-mediated inhibition of histone deacetylase 9 (HDAC9), resulting in suppression of environmental allergen hypersensitivity, propionate affects lung dendritic cells, dampening promotion of T helper type 2 cell-driven inflammation while leaving the cells' phagocytic ability intact 81,"
